  "prompt": "What is the difference between objective and subjective?",
  "response": "The difference between objective and subjective lies in the nature of the information or perspective being presented.\n\nObjective:\n- Objective information is unbiased and based on measurable facts.\n- It can be verified through evidence and observation.\n- It is not influenced by personal feelings, interpretations, or opinions.\n- For example, saying \"The temperature outside is 75 degrees Fahrenheit\" is an objective statement because it can be measured and verified.\n\nSubjective:\n- Subjective information is influenced by personal feelings, interpretations, or opinions.\n- It is based on individual perspectives and experiences.\n- It can vary from person to person and is not universally verifiable.\n- For example, saying \"It feels really hot outside\" is a subjective statement because it is based on personal sensation and opinion.\n\nIn summary, objective relates to factual and unbiased information, while subjective relates to personal and opinion-based viewpoints.",
